Mongoose is an ODM
Object Document Mapper (or Model)

Equivalent in SQL is ORM (which we didn't use)
Object Relational Model

Mongoose is only for Mongo + Node

No schemas in Mongo, but Mongoose allows you to create schema

PATCH request - for updating properties of a document without overwriting the whole thing


Services - can be used by more than one controller, i.e. $http

